Paranoia, vomiting...

23:41.238 --> 23:43.007
basically everything
except death.

23:43.040 --> 23:45.009
Nope, death as well
if you drink too much.

23:45.042 --> 23:46.744
You think
this was a hallucination?

23:46.777 --> 23:48.212
Show him the video.

24:08.933 --> 24:10.801
Hollywood.

24:10.835 --> 24:12.903
No. No, he...

24:12.937 --> 24:14.605
- thinks it's a film.
- No.

24:18.342 --> 24:20.177
This is a real video,
okay?

24:20.211 --> 24:21.779
It's real.
It's not Hollywood.

24:21.812 --> 24:23.781
Real video.

24:23.814 --> 24:24.782
Yeah, real video.

24:24.815 --> 24:25.783
These bruises
are real.

24:25.816 --> 24:27.284
I choked her, okay?

24:27.318 --> 24:28.919
I can't remember it.

24:28.953 --> 24:31.022
I can't remember
the last 12 hours.

24:43.734 --> 24:44.802
Take.

24:44.835 --> 24:45.970
I'm not going
to drink this.

24:46.003 --> 24:47.171
Everything will be okay.

24:47.204 --> 24:48.973
- I'm not drinking this.
- No.

25:01.118 --> 25:04.989
Bad medicine
on our island.

25:11.195 --> 25:12.797
Very good food.

25:21.272 --> 25:23.140
Turn it off.

25:23.174 --> 25:24.775
Turn it off!

25:24.809 --> 25:26.243
I-I don't even understand
what I'm seeing.

25:26.277 --> 25:28.679
Yeah? Well, it looks
a lot like you to me.

25:28.712 --> 25:30.948
You know that's
not me, right?

25:30.981 --> 25:33.084
I was throwing up
dirt, Neil.

25:33.117 --> 25:34.285
Well, you were
covered in it.

25:34.318 --> 25:35.786
You must have
swallowed some of it...

25:35.820 --> 25:37.655
And what about
these bruises on my neck?

25:37.688 --> 25:38.756
They're from you.

25:38.789 --> 25:39.990
From me?

25:40.024 --> 25:41.692
What's on this video
is impossible.

25:41.725 --> 25:43.794
We watched you
snap my neck!

25:43.828 --> 25:46.197
Do you understand
how insane that sounds?

25:46.230 --> 25:49.233
You're standing here right in front of
me, and you're fine.

25:50.935 --> 25:52.770
Look,
what's on this video,

25:52.803 --> 25:56.974
there must be a less crazy
explanation for what we're seeing.

25:57.007 --> 25:57.975
Right?

26:02.413 --> 26:03.914
Neil?

26:04.949 --> 26:06.050
Neil?!

26:11.422 --> 26:13.324
Neil?!

26:13.357 --> 26:14.391
Oh, my God.

26:17.895 --> 26:20.364
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

26:20.397 --> 26:22.900
Cafe is like
a two-minute walk from here

26:22.933 --> 26:24.869
Wait.
Wh-Where did you go?

26:24.902 --> 26:26.837
Where were you
just now?

26:26.871 --> 26:28.172
What are you talking about?
I just...

26:28.205 --> 26:29.240
Christine, are you okay?
Come here.

26:29.273 --> 26:30.341
- Don't.
- What?

26:33.010 --> 26:34.044
Look...

26:35.146 --> 26:37.081
I understand
you're scared, okay?

26:37.114 --> 26:40.084
I-I'm scared, too,
but don't be scared of me.

26:40.117 --> 26:42.052
I would never
intentionally hurt you.

26:44.155 --> 26:45.389
If you want some space,

26:45.422 --> 26:47.124
I can go and try
and find the passports.

26:47.158 --> 26:49.727
Are you seriously suggesting
that we split up right now?

26:49.760 --> 26:51.328
- No, I'm just saying...
- You know what?

26:51.362 --> 26:52.796
Just go take
your pictures, Neil,

26:52.830 --> 26:54.165
'cause that's
what you wanna do.

26:54.198 --> 26:57.101
I'm just trying
to do the right thing.

26:57.134 --> 26:59.270
I... Only I don't know
what that is.

27:07.244 --> 27:08.846
I just wanna go home.

27:08.879 --> 27:10.347
Seven p.m. tonight,
we're getting on that ferry,

27:10.381 --> 27:12.116
and we're getting
the hell out of here.

27:17.788 --> 27:19.890
I'm sorry. I...

27:21.292 --> 27:23.127
I don't have
any other words.

27:23.160 --> 27:26.330
I don't know
what happened last night,

27:26.363 --> 27:27.765
but whatever it was...

27:29.466 --> 27:30.868
I'm sorry.

27:48.986 --> 27:50.821
Is this
the mystery festival?

27:57.027 --> 27:58.195
Yeah, I guess.

27:58.229 --> 28:00.130
You're welcome
to get closer.

28:01.999 --> 28:03.901
Miss,
I feel dumb for asking,

28:03.934 --> 28:07.071
but what festival
is this? Miss?

28:14.845 --> 28:16.313
Bon appÃ©tit!

28:19.850 --> 28:22.052
Did you see the way
she looked at this?

28:22.086 --> 28:23.320
Yeah.

28:24.321 --> 28:26.156
So creepy.

28:26.190 --> 28:27.324
I'm done.

28:37.401 --> 28:38.936
Go.

28:38.969 --> 28:40.104
It's why you came here.

28:41.138 --> 28:42.873
It's fine.

28:42.906 --> 28:44.041
You're the best.

30:49.533 --> 30:51.135
This is Neil Oliver.

30:51.168 --> 30:52.604
It's, uh, May 10,

30:52.637 --> 30:54.438
a day of no significance

30:54.471 --> 30:56.608
on the Thai
or Buddhist calendars,

30:56.641 --> 30:59.410
but as you can see, the...

30:59.443 --> 31:01.579
the islanders are celebrating.

31:01.613 --> 31:03.514
Something... Hey! Hey! Hey!

31:05.482 --> 31:07.117
God!

31:47.524 --> 31:48.726
Hey!

31:52.229 --> 31:53.497
What are you doing?

31:53.530 --> 31:54.632
God.

32:15.753 --> 32:18.088
- Where is my wife?
- The bathroom.

32:33.437 --> 32:35.506
Christine, honey, we need to leave.

32:35.539 --> 32:36.608
Chris...

32:45.215 --> 32:46.250
Christine!

32:58.596 --> 32:59.797
Christine!

33:10.240 --> 33:11.275
Christine!

33:22.152 --> 33:23.453
Christine!

33:50.147 --> 33:51.181
Christine!

33:52.850 --> 33:55.218
Hey. Have you seen her?

33:58.556 --> 34:00.324
Hey. Have you seen her?

34:00.357 --> 34:01.593
Mr. Oliver!

34:01.626 --> 34:03.193
We found your wife!

34:07.397 --> 34:08.365
Christine!

34:14.438 --> 34:15.472
Christine?

34:15.505 --> 34:16.641
Christine, sweetheart.

34:16.674 --> 34:17.842
Say something.

34:17.875 --> 34:19.644
- Her arm!
- I got you. Got you.

34:19.677 --> 34:21.278
Yeah, I can see
her fuckin' arm.

34:21.311 --> 34:22.546
Ah, it's okay.

34:25.515 --> 34:27.685
What the fuck
happened to her, huh?

34:30.822 --> 34:32.456
Sorry.

34:32.489 --> 34:33.758
Sorry.

34:33.791 --> 34:34.759
Hurts.

34:34.792 --> 34:36.426
Aw, what happened?

34:36.460 --> 34:38.261
Huh?
Come on, sweetie.

34:38.295 --> 34:41.198
I-I must have looked around the
entire town looking for you.

34:41.231 --> 34:43.668
Where'd you go, huh?

34:43.701 --> 34:45.369
God.

34:47.504 --> 34:48.873
Did you put this back on me?

34:48.906 --> 34:50.708
What? No.

34:50.742 --> 34:53.477
I left it on the table
at the cafe.

34:53.510 --> 34:55.747
Why won't you tell me
what happened?

34:55.780 --> 34:57.447
You won't believe me.

34:58.415 --> 34:59.717
What are you
talking about?

34:59.751 --> 35:01.819
After today, try me.

35:07.558 --> 35:09.861
Let's go get this
bandaged properly, okay?

35:16.601 --> 35:18.301
When I got my vision back,

35:18.335 --> 35:20.571
I looked up at them, and they
were completely faceless.

35:20.605 --> 35:22.674
Their eyes were sewn shut.

35:22.707 --> 35:23.941
Their mouths were sewn shut.

35:26.376 --> 35:27.912
I sound totally crazy.

35:27.945 --> 35:29.914
No. No, look...

35:29.947 --> 35:31.381
I believe you.

35:31.415 --> 35:32.449
Check this out.

35:33.417 --> 35:35.318
It looks just like you.

35:35.352 --> 35:36.788
- Kind of.
- Yeah.

35:45.262 --> 35:47.264
- Wait. She gave me the necklace.
- Christine...

35:47.297 --> 35:48.566
Hey!

35:49.567 --> 35:50.601
Hey!

36:29.040 --> 36:30.775
Excuse me.

36:30.808 --> 36:32.910
There was a woman
who just left here.

36:32.944 --> 36:35.479
Can you tell us
something about her?

36:40.651 --> 36:42.053
Chakrii...

36:45.690 --> 36:46.724
My son.

36:48.092 --> 36:49.493
Needs a doctor,
don't you think?

36:50.828 --> 36:52.797
No, just rest.

36:53.931 --> 36:55.666
What do you know
about this necklace?

36:57.467 --> 36:58.703
Anything?

37:07.544 --> 37:09.312
Hey, hey, easy.
Easy.

37:15.753 --> 37:16.788
Okay.

37:18.589 --> 37:19.757
Thank you.

37:27.732 --> 37:29.000
What the fuck was that?

37:29.033 --> 37:31.569
It's an honor on our island,

37:31.602 --> 37:34.538
special gift
for celebrated guest.

37:34.572 --> 37:35.539
A celebrated guest?

37:35.573 --> 37:37.809
I'm a tourist,
all right?

37:37.842 --> 37:38.910
Do you know Madee?

37:38.943 --> 37:41.078
The woman
who just left here,

37:41.112 --> 37:42.546
she gave this to me.

37:42.580 --> 37:44.481
You want to thank her?

37:44.514 --> 37:46.117
Yes. I want to thank her

37:46.150 --> 37:47.885
for the 12 hours
that have gone missing

37:47.919 --> 37:49.352
since she gave me
this necklace.

37:49.386 --> 37:50.755
Our passports
have been stolen.

37:50.788 --> 37:52.522
I was gone again
for another hour.

37:52.557 --> 37:53.791
My husband looked
for me everywhere.

37:53.825 --> 37:54.826
He couldn't find me.

37:54.859 --> 37:56.561
He didn't know
where I was!

37:56.594 --> 37:58.830
I've been seeing shit that I
don't even know is real!

37:58.863 --> 38:00.631
It's all right.

38:03.568 --> 38:08.072
Look, we just want
to know one thing, okay?

38:08.105 --> 38:09.874
Tell us
how to find Madee.

38:24.121 --> 38:25.388
Madee's bar.

38:26.489 --> 38:28.491
I don't recommend you go.

38:28.525 --> 38:30.561
It's not for westerners.

38:30.595 --> 38:32.663
Yeah, well,
it's too late,

38:32.697 --> 38:34.431
'cause I think
we've already been.

39:39.096 --> 39:42.600
Ms. Christina,
Mr. Neil.

39:42.633 --> 39:43.834
What surprise.

39:43.868 --> 39:45.002
You ran from us.

39:45.036 --> 39:46.904
Run from you?

39:48.139 --> 39:49.640
We all look alike,
right?

39:49.674 --> 39:51.508
Come. Come.

40:01.552 --> 40:03.154
Neil, that looks
like my dress.

40:09.727 --> 40:12.596
I try to find you.

40:12.630 --> 40:14.799
You went home fast,
and you forgot it.

40:14.832 --> 40:17.500
Oh, yeah, it must have
been really tough

40:17.534 --> 40:19.937
to find two foreigners
in a town this big, huh?

40:19.971 --> 40:24.008
Everybody
are foreigners here.

40:24.041 --> 40:25.876
I came from
somewhere else...

40:27.645 --> 40:28.846
as did many.

40:30.848 --> 40:33.084
Wait. Wh-Where's the other...

40:33.117 --> 40:35.518
Where's...
Where's my wife's passport?

40:35.553 --> 40:36.754
Only you.

40:36.787 --> 40:38.656
What? Listen.

40:38.689 --> 40:41.058
After we left here
last night,

40:41.092 --> 40:43.694
I choked my wife and then
buried her in a ditch.

40:50.134 --> 40:52.770
Kinky.

40:52.803 --> 40:54.905
That's what happen when
you ride the <i>manu miti.</i>

40:54.939 --> 40:56.674
The what?

40:56.707 --> 40:57.875
Dream bird.

40:57.908 --> 41:01.879
They say it...
it opens up your mind,

41:01.912 --> 41:03.714
free your soul.

41:03.748 --> 41:05.750
But I wouldn't touch it.

41:06.784 --> 41:08.518
Too many side effects.

41:10.154 --> 41:12.189
Like hallucination,

41:12.223 --> 41:14.959
scramble the brain.

41:14.992 --> 41:18.129
So you wouldn't take it,
but you serve it?

41:22.900 --> 41:25.002
My friend,
you're the one

41:25.036 --> 41:27.571
who asked
for the drink yourself,

41:27.605 --> 41:29.140
and I rewarded you...

41:29.173 --> 41:30.841
for your bravery.

41:30.875 --> 41:32.143
Take your bravery back.

41:32.176 --> 41:34.111
No.

41:34.145 --> 41:36.313
It's not yours
to give.

41:36.347 --> 41:38.182
What the hell
does that even mean?

41:38.215 --> 41:40.184
I am so sick
of this cryptic bullshit.

41:49.026 --> 41:50.661
What happened last night?

41:50.694 --> 41:53.164
And where is my passport?

41:55.332 --> 41:57.668
I think we should
get out of here.

42:05.276 --> 42:06.710
I'll see you around.

43:28.726 --> 43:32.096
Hey, one of Samantha's
neighbors is a fisherman.

43:32.129 --> 43:34.331
He's gonna take us
to the mainland now.

43:34.365 --> 43:35.833
What? Really?

43:37.301 --> 43:38.335
No!

43:39.970 --> 43:41.372
You can't go.

43:41.405 --> 43:43.174
Isn't
the ferry at 7:00?

43:43.207 --> 43:45.776
We found another boat that
will take us off the island.

43:45.809 --> 43:48.045
They have to go back
to their own home, sweetie.

43:49.346 --> 43:51.949
Why don't you help Neil
with the bags, okay?

43:51.982 --> 43:54.084
O-Okay. Uh...

43:54.118 --> 43:55.886
lead the way.

43:58.155 --> 43:59.924
He'll make a great father.

44:05.429 --> 44:07.131
Thank you
for everything.

44:07.164 --> 44:08.432
Oh...

44:08.465 --> 44:10.234
And the juice made me
feel so much better.

44:10.267 --> 44:11.936
Oh, yeah?
Island magic, right,

44:11.969 --> 44:14.038
just like your necklace.

44:15.339 --> 44:18.075
What is that?
Is that a real thing?

44:18.108 --> 44:20.211
Or is that
just superstition?

44:21.278 --> 44:22.846
I mean,
I used to think so.

44:22.880 --> 44:24.848
But I used to be
really sick.

44:24.882 --> 44:27.818
I went to a specialist
in America, Canada, China.

44:27.851 --> 44:31.021
Finally someone said
I should come to this island.

44:31.055 --> 44:32.289
I had no idea
what to expect.

44:32.323 --> 44:33.891
I mean, I thought
I was gonna meet

44:33.924 --> 44:35.526
a witch doctor or something,
not that I care.

44:35.560 --> 44:37.895
I mean, at that point,
everything was on the table.

44:37.928 --> 44:41.031
But, uh, I got here.

44:42.499 --> 44:44.468
I don't know.
It was the best thing for me.

44:44.501 --> 44:45.836
I haven't been sick since.

44:45.869 --> 44:48.205
So whether you
call that clean air,

44:48.239 --> 44:50.241
climate, or magic,
I'll take it.

44:50.274 --> 44:52.309
Well, listen.

44:52.343 --> 44:54.445
I-I'm not a believer.

44:54.478 --> 44:56.213
You clearly are, so...

44:56.247 --> 44:58.249
why don't you
just take this?

44:58.282 --> 45:00.184
I can't, no.

45:00.217 --> 45:02.820
It's, uh...
It's not meant for me.

45:02.853 --> 45:05.356
You should probably
just keep it for good luck.

45:08.459 --> 45:09.860
Right.

45:11.295 --> 45:13.364
Well, look, if you're
ever in Boston...

45:13.397 --> 45:16.800
Ah, I did 26 years
in Minnesota,

45:16.834 --> 45:18.502
so if you're lucky
enough to find paradise,

45:18.535 --> 45:20.170
why try to leave, right?

46:02.614 --> 46:05.149
Hey. I was
just thinking.

46:05.182 --> 46:06.551
No one knows
where we are.

46:06.584 --> 46:08.018
What are you talking about?

46:08.052 --> 46:09.621
Well, we were supposed
to be on a flight

46:09.654 --> 46:11.589
to the States
this afternoon.

46:11.623 --> 46:13.090
Let me borrow
your phone.

46:15.993 --> 46:17.194
Honey?

46:17.227 --> 46:18.262
Your phone.

46:19.263 --> 46:20.497
Who are you gonna call?

46:20.531 --> 46:21.999
My Dad. My sister.

46:22.032 --> 46:23.367
The FBI. I don't know.

46:23.400 --> 46:25.969
Who did the guy
in <i>The Wicker Man</i> call?

46:26.003 --> 46:28.439
No one. They
burned him to death.

46:28.472 --> 46:30.040
Oh, yeah.

46:30.074 --> 46:32.343
He didn't have
a cell phone, though.

46:32.376 --> 46:34.945
I'm gonna try
and get reception.

46:34.978 --> 46:36.080
I love you.

46:58.435 --> 46:59.937
Come on.

46:59.970 --> 47:01.138
Come on, come on, come on.

47:28.566 --> 47:29.601
<i>This is Neil Oliver</i>

47:29.634 --> 47:31.669
<i>taking you off the beaten path.</i>

47:31.703 --> 47:33.537
<i>For my travel companion
and I,</i>

47:33.571 --> 47:36.073
<i>there's no hope of us
ever leaving this island.</i>

47:36.106 --> 47:37.575
- What the fuck?
- <i>Christine,</i>

47:37.609 --> 47:39.644
<i>we're about to die
horrible deaths.</i>

48:08.439 --> 48:09.540
Neil?

48:42.674 --> 48:44.308
Neil!

49:07.699 --> 49:09.166
Neil!

49:59.684 --> 50:01.485
Where's my husband?

50:03.788 --> 50:05.757
No, where's my husband?

50:07.592 --> 50:08.626
My husband!

50:12.129 --> 50:13.163
There was a boat!

50:14.197 --> 50:16.099
Where did he go?!

50:17.735 --> 50:18.770
Neil!

50:20.270 --> 50:22.640
No, he...

50:29.914 --> 50:31.381
Where is he?

50:34.652 --> 50:36.486
I-I saw him.

50:36.520 --> 50:37.589
He...

50:38.590 --> 50:42.159
He cut...
He cut himself open,

50:42.192 --> 50:43.728
and then he...

50:43.761 --> 50:46.664
he fell off
the end of the dock

50:51.903 --> 50:53.638
See this blood?

50:53.671 --> 50:55.272
This is...
This is his blood.

50:55.305 --> 50:57.441
H-He's on the dock.

50:57.474 --> 50:59.744
Uh...

50:59.777 --> 51:01.411
- Fish. Fish.
- No.

51:01.445 --> 51:03.681
No! No!

51:03.715 --> 51:05.248
How did
nobody see this?

51:06.784 --> 51:07.919
The tide
is out then.

51:07.952 --> 51:09.152
There couldn't
have been a boat.

51:09.186 --> 51:10.354
There was a boat.

51:10.387 --> 51:11.623
Oh, God.

51:12.624 --> 51:14.659
Hey! You!

51:14.692 --> 51:16.594
You saw the boat
and the water!

51:16.628 --> 51:18.328
You saw me, right,

51:18.362 --> 51:20.297
and my husband
on the dock?

51:21.566 --> 51:23.333
Uh...

51:25.268 --> 51:28.205
Christine...

51:28.238 --> 51:29.272
...Neil.

51:30.975 --> 51:32.744
He... He said one.

51:32.777 --> 51:34.511
He said it was
just you, not Neil.

51:34.544 --> 51:35.647
He said only one.

51:35.680 --> 51:38.583
Wh-What is he trying to do?

51:39.617 --> 51:40.618
What is he trying to do?

51:40.652 --> 51:41.786
What is...

51:41.819 --> 51:43.721
- Just calm down, please.
- Oh, God.

51:45.288 --> 51:46.323
Witnesses
heard you screaming.

51:46.356 --> 51:47.424
Wait. Where's his phone?

51:47.457 --> 51:48.458
His... His phone?

51:50.293 --> 51:51.763
- You camera?
- No, his phone.

51:51.796 --> 51:52.764
On him.

51:52.797 --> 51:54.599
No, I had it.

51:54.632 --> 51:56.199
I had it.
Somebody took it.

51:57.534 --> 51:59.336
Uh, he said, "Did you
and Neil fight?"

51:59.369 --> 52:01.706
No! No!

52:01.739 --> 52:04.942
My husband and I
were fine!

52:04.976 --> 52:06.911
Oh, my God,
what are you doing?

52:06.944 --> 52:08.345
What is he doing?!

52:08.378 --> 52:09.914
What is this?

52:09.947 --> 52:12.817
No, why don't you
come on? Come on.

52:32.536 --> 52:36.641
Hey, you should
drink something.

54:28.953 --> 54:30.320
Neil!

54:32.890 --> 54:33.891
Neil.

54:36.828 --> 54:39.931
Neil! Neil.

54:58.481 --> 54:59.516
Christine!

55:00.483 --> 55:02.053
Christine, it's Neil...

55:02.086 --> 55:03.621
on the phone!

55:03.654 --> 55:06.389
Huh? Huh?

55:10.695 --> 55:12.730
Neil?

55:14.632 --> 55:15.600
Neil?

55:16.901 --> 55:18.636
Honey?

55:18.669 --> 55:20.037
Neil, speak up, honey.

55:20.071 --> 55:21.504
I can't hear you.

55:22.539 --> 55:24.976
Hello? Hello?

55:30.547 --> 55:32.149
I lost the signal.

55:32.183 --> 55:33.918
- What did he say?
- I just...

55:33.951 --> 55:35.553
The reception was bad.

55:35.586 --> 55:37.420
He just said,
"Neil," and...

55:37.454 --> 55:38.990
Did he say he was okay?

55:39.023 --> 55:41.659
I just ran
to give you the phone.

55:43.027 --> 55:44.729
Oh, this is bullshit.

55:44.762 --> 55:46.197
Somebody's messing with us.

55:46.230 --> 55:49.200
Do you want to call
the police?

55:49.233 --> 55:50.568
I know who's doing this.

55:53.604 --> 55:55.006
I know where he is.

56:14.792 --> 56:16.493
<i>A typhoon warning
is in effect...</i>

56:21.799 --> 56:24.201
<i>Typhoon Maicala,
a major typhoon</i>

56:24.235 --> 56:27.705
<i>is poised to make landfall
in five hours.</i>

56:27.738 --> 56:29.607
<i>Expect pounding rain,
flash flooding...</i>

56:29.640 --> 56:31.175
What are you and
Nathida going to do?

56:31.208 --> 56:33.177
<i>...240 kilometers per hour.</i>

56:33.210 --> 56:37.014
A storm hasn't hit
the island in 200 years.

56:38.716 --> 56:41.185
<i>...could sweep away
anything not nailed down.</i>

56:41.218 --> 56:43.187
<i>Just to put this
in context for you...</i>

56:45.289 --> 56:49.794
<i>...winds of
130 kilometers an hour.</i>

56:49.827 --> 56:52.563
<i>It is shaping up to be
the storm of the year,</i>

56:52.596 --> 56:53.898
<i>if not the decade,
and it's already</i>

56:53.931 --> 56:56.834
<i>been classified
as a super typhoon.</i>

57:06.543 --> 57:09.046
This is the part where I
tell you not to go in.

57:10.681 --> 57:12.717
This is part
where I don't listen.

57:17.288 --> 57:18.556
Neil!

57:24.128 --> 57:25.495
Neil!

57:29.300 --> 57:30.533
Honey?

58:12.143 --> 58:14.011
Where is my husband?

58:42.239 --> 58:44.241
Mommy.

58:44.275 --> 58:46.010
Whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, hey.

58:46.043 --> 58:48.779
Easy. Easy. Hey.

58:49.747 --> 58:51.015
How did I get here?

58:52.383 --> 58:54.151
You don't remember?

58:54.185 --> 58:55.352
Whoa!

59:05.930 --> 59:08.699
How did I
get back here?

59:08.732 --> 59:12.770
Uh, as soon as you left
the car, you passed out.

59:12.803 --> 59:14.705
You collapsed
right in front of us.

59:14.738 --> 59:16.307
No, that's not possible.

59:16.340 --> 59:17.942
You don't remember?

59:17.975 --> 59:19.977
I need a minute, please.

59:20.945 --> 59:22.913
Yeah, sure.

1:00:24.308 --> 1:00:25.342
Neil?

1:00:26.510 --> 1:00:28.045
Christine?

1:00:30.281 --> 1:00:31.882
What's happening?

1:00:31.916 --> 1:00:33.384
I don't...

1:00:33.417 --> 1:00:34.919
Where is it?

1:00:34.952 --> 1:00:36.287
What?

1:00:36.320 --> 1:00:37.688
This?

1:00:46.230 --> 1:00:48.265
I've heard
of those things

1:00:48.299 --> 1:00:52.069
healing the sick,
healing worse.

1:00:52.102 --> 1:00:54.238
You need to see
a doctor.

1:00:55.773 --> 1:00:57.107
If Neil were here...

1:00:57.141 --> 1:00:58.175
He's not.

1:00:59.410 --> 1:01:01.979
It was in your head,
what you saw.

1:01:02.012 --> 1:01:04.148
Neil didn't kill himself
at the end of my dock.

1:01:04.181 --> 1:01:05.282
Then what happened?

1:01:07.218 --> 1:01:08.485
He, uh...

1:01:09.954 --> 1:01:11.789
He showed me
the video.

1:01:14.491 --> 1:01:16.160
Why would he do that?

1:01:16.193 --> 1:01:17.895
I...

1:01:17.928 --> 1:01:20.464
He was freaking out when I
found you in the bathroom.

1:01:20.497 --> 1:01:23.100
He said he didn't
know how or why,

1:01:23.133 --> 1:01:25.970
and he was scared
he would do it again.

1:01:26.003 --> 1:01:28.205
And you're
just telling me this now?!

1:01:28.239 --> 1:01:31.442
If I saw a video of me
putting hands on my daughter,

1:01:31.475 --> 1:01:34.378
I'd wanna get as far away
from her as possible.

1:01:35.580 --> 1:01:37.348
Look, I know
you don't trust me.

1:01:37.381 --> 1:01:39.783
You don't
even know me.

1:01:41.418 --> 1:01:42.920
But whatever is
going on with you,

1:01:42.953 --> 1:01:44.255
you need
to see a doctor.

1:01:44.288 --> 1:01:46.257
I'll do it when I
get back to the mainland.

1:01:46.290 --> 1:01:48.993
You need
a doctor from here.

1:01:50.294 --> 1:01:51.996
Christine.

1:02:08.345 --> 1:02:10.781
Hmm.

1:02:12.149 --> 1:02:13.117
You are pregnant.

1:02:19.089 --> 1:02:20.924
That's not possible.

1:02:20.958 --> 1:02:23.595
Our island is good
for fertility.

1:02:23.628 --> 1:02:26.297
Pregnant women
are sacred here.

1:02:27.531 --> 1:02:29.567
Neil will be
so happy.

1:02:29.601 --> 1:02:31.368
Congratulations.

1:02:31.402 --> 1:02:32.536
That's not happening.

1:02:32.570 --> 1:02:34.204
There's no way.

1:02:38.208 --> 1:02:40.144
Do you want to see?

1:02:55.225 --> 1:02:56.427
Oh, my God.

1:02:57.461 --> 1:02:58.996
That's amazing.

1:02:59.029 --> 1:03:01.599
Is that
the heartbeat?

1:03:01.633 --> 1:03:03.334
Yeah.

1:03:07.971 --> 1:03:12.443
Doctor,
this hallucination?

1:03:12.476 --> 1:03:13.645
<i>Nam Mun Prai?</i>

1:03:13.678 --> 1:03:16.413
No. No <i>Nam Mun Prai.</i>

1:03:22.252 --> 1:03:25.189
They said
it wasn't possible.

1:03:43.575 --> 1:03:46.210
What was that?

1:03:46.243 --> 1:03:48.145
He wants you to relax.
He's worried about you.

1:03:49.146 --> 1:03:50.147
Oh, no.
Don't you dare.

1:03:50.180 --> 1:03:52.082
Don't you dare!

1:03:53.685 --> 1:03:55.386
Wait! Christine,
wait! It's ok...

1:04:14.037 --> 1:04:15.506
What is this?

1:04:16.741 --> 1:04:19.076
What's happening?

1:04:19.109 --> 1:04:21.378
Storm.
You need to leave.

1:04:21.412 --> 1:04:23.347
I haven't found Neil yet.

1:04:23.380 --> 1:04:25.449
My... My husband.

1:04:27.151 --> 1:04:28.452
No husband.

1:04:28.485 --> 1:04:30.354
Ride?

1:04:30.387 --> 1:04:32.624
Boat?

1:04:32.657 --> 1:04:36.260
I... No, I don't want
a ride or... or a boat.

1:04:36.293 --> 1:04:38.730
I need to find my husband,
and then I'll get a ride.

1:04:41.498 --> 1:04:44.501
Can I borrow your...
your phone?

1:04:44.535 --> 1:04:45.969
Your cell phone?

1:04:49.406 --> 1:04:51.275
No service.

1:04:51.308 --> 1:04:52.309
Of course.

1:05:20.805 --> 1:05:22.339
Hello?

1:05:24.408 --> 1:05:25.743
Hello?

1:05:29.480 --> 1:05:30.648
Kanda?

1:05:48.833 --> 1:05:50.768
I'm pregnant.

1:05:52.804 --> 1:05:56.006
Stop.
You already know that.

1:05:59.476 --> 1:06:04.348
There was a time when everybody
didn't have a phone in their pocket.

1:06:06.350 --> 1:06:08.553
You were never meant
to see what happened.

1:06:10.688 --> 1:06:13.323
You would have
remained unaware.

1:06:13.357 --> 1:06:15.492
I am brutally aware
that my husband

1:06:15.526 --> 1:06:17.629
forced himself on me
and then strangled me.

1:06:17.662 --> 1:06:19.096
Forced?

1:06:19.129 --> 1:06:22.099
No, encouraged...

1:06:22.132 --> 1:06:24.234
to create a new life.

1:06:24.268 --> 1:06:26.136
Being pregnant,

1:06:26.169 --> 1:06:28.071
there is no stronger spirit
in our faith.

1:06:28.105 --> 1:06:30.642
No, no, stop.
I was dead, okay?

1:06:30.675 --> 1:06:33.176
I saw the video.
How am I standing here?

1:06:34.579 --> 1:06:38.115
Not quite dead.
Not quite living.

1:06:38.148 --> 1:06:41.518
That necklace keeps
the scales from tipping

1:06:41.553 --> 1:06:42.854
in the wrong direction.

1:06:42.887 --> 1:06:47.157
Right now, you exist
on the spiritual plane,

1:06:47.190 --> 1:06:49.861
where the spirits can prepare
you for the final ritual.

1:06:49.894 --> 1:06:51.161
I know this sounds...

1:06:51.194 --> 1:06:52.730
Fucking insane? Yeah.

1:06:57.267 --> 1:06:59.336
For hundreds of years,

1:06:59.369 --> 1:07:01.305
they have been
burying pregnant women

1:07:01.338 --> 1:07:03.708
under the post
of the town square.

1:07:03.741 --> 1:07:07.812
They believe that these sacrifices
get them what they want,

1:07:07.845 --> 1:07:09.513
to keep the island safe.

1:07:09.546 --> 1:07:12.817
and tonight,
they sacrifice you to stop the storm.

1:07:16.486 --> 1:07:18.690
Oh, fuck that.
I can't even believe

1:07:18.723 --> 1:07:20.324
this conversation
we're having right now.

1:07:20.357 --> 1:07:21.893
Are you kidding me?

1:07:21.926 --> 1:07:23.661
The man that I've loved
since I was 19,

1:07:23.695 --> 1:07:26.430
he conspired to kill me by
order of these crazy people.

1:07:27.932 --> 1:07:29.567
It wasn't him.

1:07:31.636 --> 1:07:32.737
<i>Nam Mun Prai...</i>

1:07:34.639 --> 1:07:36.540
corpse oil.

1:07:36.574 --> 1:07:39.376
It can control your mind.

1:07:39.409 --> 1:07:42.279
They gave it to Neil,
and he buried you in our soil.

1:07:47.752 --> 1:07:52.824
My son, he doesn't
have much time left,

1:07:52.857 --> 1:07:55.325
days, maybe weeks.

1:07:56.460 --> 1:07:59.296
I don't believe
in their rituals.

1:07:59.329 --> 1:08:02.867
I don't believe an unwilling
sacrifice can stop the storm,

1:08:02.900 --> 1:08:05.535
but I do
believe in that.

1:08:05.570 --> 1:08:08.606
It has
the power to heal.

1:08:08.640 --> 1:08:12.442
I can help you
if you help my son.

1:08:12.476 --> 1:08:14.177
Just give me
the necklace...

1:08:14.211 --> 1:08:18.181
No, not until you
help me find my husband

1:08:18.215 --> 1:08:20.852
and get us
off this fucking island.

1:08:20.885 --> 1:08:22.754
Then you can have
whatever you want.

1:09:01.626 --> 1:09:02.827
Ahh!

1:10:01.986 --> 1:10:03.320
No, no, no.

1:10:03.353 --> 1:10:06.023
You need a doctor.

1:10:10.494 --> 1:10:12.029
My... My son.

1:10:25.743 --> 1:10:27.612
Sorry.

1:10:30.047 --> 1:10:31.281
Okay.

1:10:52.003 --> 1:10:53.037
Kanda?

1:11:00.443 --> 1:11:01.846
Oh, no. Oh, no.

1:11:10.054 --> 1:11:11.622
Run!

1:11:11.656 --> 1:11:13.558
Oh, God.
Oh, God.

1:11:21.866 --> 1:11:22.900
Run.

1:11:35.947 --> 1:11:37.081
Hello?

1:11:37.114 --> 1:11:38.716
Is anybody...

1:11:38.749 --> 1:11:40.450
I need help.

1:11:40.483 --> 1:11:42.019
Shit.

1:11:42.053 --> 1:11:43.855
Excuse me.
Can you help me?

1:11:45.923 --> 1:11:47.959
Can you help me?

1:11:47.992 --> 1:11:49.392
Can you help?

1:11:51.996 --> 1:11:53.496
Excuse me.

1:11:53.530 --> 1:11:54.799
I need...

1:12:00.872 --> 1:12:01.973
Excuse me!

1:12:03.040 --> 1:12:05.142
I need a phone.
Can you help me?

1:12:05.176 --> 1:12:06.143
No, no, no.

1:12:06.177 --> 1:12:07.612
Christine, oh, my God.

1:12:07.645 --> 1:12:09.412
I've been looking
everywhere for you.

1:12:09.446 --> 1:12:11.414
She's dead.

1:12:11.448 --> 1:12:12.583
Who?

1:12:12.617 --> 1:12:14.517
- Kanda.
- God.

1:12:14.552 --> 1:12:16.519
Come on.
Let's get you out of here.

1:12:16.554 --> 1:12:17.922
Are you taking me
to the ferry?

1:12:17.955 --> 1:12:20.157
Yeah. Come on.

1:12:21.491 --> 1:12:22.927
Why are you
dressed like them?

1:12:22.960 --> 1:12:24.562
What, this?
This is for the festival.

1:12:24.595 --> 1:12:26.597
Come on. I just parked
over here. Let's go.

1:12:35.106 --> 1:12:37.808
<i>Right now, the typhoon
is only 1 1/2 hours away,</i>

1:12:37.842 --> 1:12:40.211
<i>so if you are still
within the path of the typhoon,</i>

1:12:40.244 --> 1:12:41.979
<i>then you need to evacuate</i>

1:12:42.013 --> 1:12:43.948
<i>or get yourself
to somewhere safe immediately.</i>

1:12:43.981 --> 1:12:46.684
<i>If your power goes out,
remain calm.</i>

1:12:46.717 --> 1:12:48.185
Mom, this isn't
the way to the ferry.

1:12:48.219 --> 1:12:49.687
It's a shortcut.

1:12:49.720 --> 1:12:51.956
This is
against the rules.

1:12:51.989 --> 1:12:53.024
Nathida.

1:12:54.025 --> 1:12:55.458
Sorry. She plays
these games.

1:12:55.492 --> 1:12:56.761
Sweetie, Mama needs
to concentrate, okay?

1:12:56.794 --> 1:12:59.230
She wants to go
to the ferry.

1:12:59.263 --> 1:13:01.498
You have
to take her.

1:13:04.001 --> 1:13:05.069
Stop the car.

1:13:05.102 --> 1:13:06.671
I'm taking you
to the ferry.

1:13:06.704 --> 1:13:08.706
Stop lying.

1:13:10.507 --> 1:13:11.575
Mommy...

1:13:11.609 --> 1:13:12.843
she knows.

1:13:17.514 --> 1:13:18.816
I'm not a bad person.

1:13:19.817 --> 1:13:21.552
What happened
to my husband?

1:13:25.957 --> 1:13:28.192
You saw Kanda's son.

1:13:28.225 --> 1:13:31.696
That's what happens when you only
believe when it's convenient.

1:13:31.729 --> 1:13:33.798
This, this is
the real deal.

1:13:33.831 --> 1:13:35.132
The real deal?

1:13:35.166 --> 1:13:36.834
Ritual sacrifice?

1:13:39.270 --> 1:13:42.606
Kanda used to believe,
and her son was fine.

1:13:42.640 --> 1:13:44.108
You're bat-shit fucking crazy.
You know that?

1:13:44.141 --> 1:13:46.677
- I love my daughter!
- Your daughter?

1:13:46.711 --> 1:13:48.980
Back there was the first time
you ever saw an ultrasound.

1:13:51.215 --> 1:13:52.717
She's not
very good at this.

1:13:52.750 --> 1:13:53.784
Shut up, Nathida!

1:13:56.988 --> 1:13:58.022
Where's your Mom?

1:13:59.924 --> 1:14:01.859
Stop lying.

1:14:03.027 --> 1:14:04.829
Where is your Mom?

1:14:06.330 --> 1:14:08.566
Down below.

1:14:13.070 --> 1:14:14.805
She loved this island.

1:14:16.007 --> 1:14:18.676
It was a sacrifice
she was happy to make.

1:14:18.709 --> 1:14:19.744
It's an honor.

1:14:20.711 --> 1:14:21.912
You killed her mother?

1:14:21.946 --> 1:14:23.546
I didn't do anything.

1:14:23.581 --> 1:14:25.082
She volunteered.

1:14:25.116 --> 1:14:28.219
She loved this island
and her little girl.

1:14:28.252 --> 1:14:29.920
I said I was sick
when I came here.

1:14:29.954 --> 1:14:32.156
Stage-three
pancreatic cancer.

1:14:32.189 --> 1:14:36.327
But here, there's
no such thing as cancer,

1:14:36.360 --> 1:14:40.164
heart attacks, stroke,
not for those who believe.

1:14:40.197 --> 1:14:42.166
That life
growing inside of you

1:14:42.199 --> 1:14:44.635
when it wasn't possible
everywhere else...

1:14:45.903 --> 1:14:49.240
Yeah.
A gift this island gave you.

1:14:49.273 --> 1:14:52.810
This is some bastardized
fanatical backwash

1:14:52.843 --> 1:14:55.946
that you soulless
motherfuckers came up with

1:14:55.980 --> 1:14:59.050
to... to feel like you
have some kind of control,

1:14:59.083 --> 1:15:01.018
that you have a say
in any of this!

1:15:01.052 --> 1:15:02.653
Where the fuck
is my husband?!

1:15:02.686 --> 1:15:05.322
Your husband is dead,
Christine.

1:15:05.356 --> 1:15:08.926
He killed himself
right in front of your eyes.

1:15:08.959 --> 1:15:10.661
That is this island,

1:15:10.694 --> 1:15:12.696
and its people
believe in something

1:15:12.730 --> 1:15:14.932
far greater than you
or your fucking...

1:16:35.112 --> 1:16:37.948
Ms. Christine.

1:20:03.253 --> 1:20:05.022
What are we doing here?

1:20:52.570 --> 1:20:55.072
Will you just let me go?

1:20:55.105 --> 1:20:58.475
For generation, it was a great honor, Ms.
Christine,

1:20:58.509 --> 1:21:00.411
to be marked as celebrated.

1:21:02.212 --> 1:21:03.414
And tonight
we celebrate you.

1:21:06.383 --> 1:21:10.020
We thank you
for your gift...

1:21:11.155 --> 1:21:12.523
for our island.

1:21:17.161 --> 1:21:20.097
And at all times,
people volunteer for this honor.

1:21:20.130 --> 1:21:21.733
You should be proud.

1:21:21.766 --> 1:21:23.333
Volunteer?

1:21:23.367 --> 1:21:26.003
I didn't volunteer
for this. Fuck you!

1:21:26.036 --> 1:21:28.172
The drink,
you asked for.

1:21:28.205 --> 1:21:30.642
The necklace,
you accept.

1:21:30.675 --> 1:21:33.343
No. We had some shots,

1:21:33.377 --> 1:21:36.180
and you put some stupid
trinket around my neck.

1:21:36.213 --> 1:21:37.514
You did that.

1:21:37.548 --> 1:21:41.151
You had free will,
Ms. Christine.

1:21:41.185 --> 1:21:45.690
You could have left, but you chose to
stay, find your husband.

1:21:47.625 --> 1:21:50.093
There were boats,
Ms. Christine.

1:21:51.663 --> 1:21:53.565
I believe
he offered you one.

1:22:01.205 --> 1:22:03.575
Because free will
is so essential.

1:22:03.608 --> 1:22:08.011
Of course, something,
free will is an illusion.

1:22:08.045 --> 1:22:09.379
You saw Neil died,

1:22:09.413 --> 1:22:11.515
but you chose
not to leave.

1:22:11.548 --> 1:22:13.551
No.

1:22:13.585 --> 1:22:17.589
Did you just not run
right to us right here

1:22:17.622 --> 1:22:20.190
at our old city pillar?

1:22:59.463 --> 1:23:01.098
Don't fucking touch me.

1:23:02.266 --> 1:23:04.034
I'm not pregnant,
you motherfucker!

1:23:05.770 --> 1:23:09.106
Pregnant,
you very much are.

1:23:09.139 --> 1:23:12.509
She is one part
from your husband

1:23:12.543 --> 1:23:16.280
and one part
from this island.

1:23:16.313 --> 1:23:18.282
No, what did you
put inside me?

1:23:22.720 --> 1:23:24.689
Island magic.

1:23:32.129 --> 1:23:33.598
I never had free will.

1:23:35.265 --> 1:23:37.200
If I have free will,
untie me.

1:23:40.337 --> 1:23:41.538
You don't have
to believe it...

1:23:41.573 --> 1:23:43.206
but we do.

1:23:44.308 --> 1:23:45.610
We will honor our gods.

1:24:21.345 --> 1:24:23.213
What are we doing here?

1:24:30.622 --> 1:24:32.189
It's a girl.

1:24:42.299 --> 1:24:44.301
You're going
to be a great Dad.

1:24:44.334 --> 1:24:46.436
She's gonna do
amazing things.

1:24:46.470 --> 1:24:48.472
Both of you are
gonna do amazing things.

1:24:49.907 --> 1:24:51.843
But I need you
to wake up.

1:24:54.544 --> 1:24:56.146
I wanna stay here.

1:25:00.652 --> 1:25:02.419
Wake up!

1:25:20.605 --> 1:25:23.808
Stop! It has
to be her choice!

1:25:23.841 --> 1:25:24.976
Stay back!

1:25:25.009 --> 1:25:27.210
Stay the fuck back.

1:25:27.244 --> 1:25:28.713
You, where's your boat?

1:25:28.746 --> 1:25:30.748
You!

1:25:30.782 --> 1:25:32.784
If you go, I'll die.

1:25:32.817 --> 1:25:35.586
They'll all die.

1:25:42.459 --> 1:25:44.494
It's not real, Nathida.
It's just a storm.

1:25:44.528 --> 1:25:45.830
- It is real!
- No!

1:25:45.863 --> 1:25:47.330
Come with me.

1:25:47.364 --> 1:25:48.733
Save us, Christine.

1:27:44.715 --> 1:27:46.751
<i>Reports are
coming in from Thailand</i>

1:27:46.784 --> 1:27:48.686
<i>that super typhoon Maicala</i>

1:27:48.719 --> 1:27:51.722
<i>has bypassed
the majority of the islands,</i>

1:27:51.756 --> 1:27:54.058
<i>with the exception
of the tiny island</i>

1:27:54.091 --> 1:27:55.660
<i>of Little Ko Kut.</i>

1:27:55.693 --> 1:27:57.128
<i>Ko Kut hasn't seen a storm</i>

1:27:57.161 --> 1:27:59.764
<i>of this magnitude
in over 200 years,</i>

1:27:59.797 --> 1:28:02.900
<i>so long, in fact, that they
advertise this to tourists.</i>

